<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-03-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="181" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                    <head>No. 181.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sargent</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-03-08"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 8,
                            1883</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Sargent telegraphs that he immediately presented the request of the
                        President, and that while Bundesrath’s action was adverse, he again
                        protested strongly; asked an answer to the President’s proposal and
                        suspension of action.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>